reviewText:
Fun adventure/interrogation game. Interesting plot and characters. Good acting, environments, and cinematography. Nice music. Even with a mere handful of characters and locations, the world feels rich, and teeming with possibilities. The keyboard controls are strange, and my Xbox 360 controller didn't work, but I managed to get used to it all in good time. I sunk a solid 8 hours into this game, and when I solved the mystery, it left me wanting more! Not something I can say after spending the same price (or more) at the theatre. ;}

About that ending (killer not mentioned, but spoilerish):
It was a bit of a twist, but it felt realistic and clever, if a bit anticlimactic. I was expecting some grand revelation about Atlas's dirty deeds, but maybe I'll get my wish if that sequel is made!

Brilliant work, Tim and company! I hope this game becomes a series. =}

helpfulPercent:
 but still portraying the characters well. Never a “cringe” moment. The story and writing is solid and deep enough to mostly keep you guessing. And develops a full atmosphere. Then the cinematography or whatever you want to call it is great within the context of it being a game. Exteriors are particularly well framed.

But it is rough around the edges as I mentioned;

-The “along for the ride” straight line story and not being able to accuse anyone or effect outcomes might bother some but I enjoyed it. Nice casual experience. You don't change the story or have options
